  <brief_title>AVANDAMET Versus Metformin And Sulphonylurea In People With Poorly Controlled Type 2 Diabetes</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Randomised, Multi-Centre, Phase IV, Double-Blind, Parallel Group Study Comparing the Effects of 52 Weeks Administration of AVANDAMET and Metformin Plus Sulphonylurea on Change in HbA1c From Baseline in Overweight Type 2 Diabetics Poorly Controlled on Metformin.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>GlaxoSmithKline</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>GlaxoSmithKline</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study compares the effects of Avandamet (rosiglitazone maleate/metformin) treatment and
      metformin plus sulphonylurea treatment in overweight people with type 2 diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
